The Lagos State Environmental and Special Offences Unit (Task Force) has arraigned an alleged fake female house agent, Mrs. Bukola Ayorinde, at a Lagos Mobile Court for defrauding unsuspecting customers seeking accommodation in Ikorodu area of the State. Ayorinde was arrested by the officials of the agency after defrauding her latest victim, Mrs. Olusola Ola-John, the sum of N250.000. The Chairman of the Agency, CSP Olayinka Egbeyemi, through a statement released by the Agency’s Head of Public Affairs Unit, Adebayo Taofiq, stated that the accused was arrested following the series of complaints from members of the public over some fake house agents obtaining a large sum of money from them and absconding.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-808810" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/944660BE-422A-43B9-9EE8-D8EEC618293D.jpeg" alt="" width="677" height="839" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/944660BE-422A-43B9-9EE8-D8EEC618293D.jpeg 677w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/944660BE-422A-43B9-9EE8-D8EEC618293D-242x300.jpeg 242w" sizes="(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px"> According to him, the Agency acted on a petition received from one Mrs. Olusola Ola-John, who claimed she was defrauded of the sum of N250,000 over securing an apartment for her aged mother at Millennium Estate Igbe in Ikorodu by the suspect. He stated that after a thorough investigation, it was discovered that the suspect was the same person who had been defrauding innocent members of the public, claiming to be a house agent around Ikorodu axis. “The suspect was charged for ‘Conduct Likely To Cause Breach Of Peace, Cheating and Obtaining N250,000 Under False Pretense’ before Chief Magistrate Abimbola Oshodi-Makanju of the Lagos State Mobile Court sitting at Bolade in Oshodi,” he said. Meanwhile, the suspect was said to have pleaded guilty to the three-count charge while the presiding magistrate adjourned the case till Friday, 26th of June, 2020 for a ‘fact and sentence’ judgment. “While appealing to the members of the public to be wary of these criminal elements when securing accommodation in any parts of the State, the Chairman confirmed that it was in line with the directive of the Lagos State Commissioner of Police, CP Hakeem Odumosu that the suspect be charged to court for prosecution,” the statement read.